snippet.textDisplay: A pretty weak Direct, but I suppose it is a 'mini'. But it has been so long since a regular Direct, this worries me for when we will actually be getting one. Are we really going to be waiting till E3 for another Direct with actual significant game announcements in it? This mini contained updates for games like Smash, Bravely Default 2, Xenoblade and Animal Crossing, but no big title was announced. Is Animal Crossing really the only big title this year?

snippet.textDisplay:
Wow, Arms in Smash? I honestly thought Nintendo and everyone else had forgotten about that game.

On a slightly more disappointing note, it's a shame that Nintendo doesn't seem to have much to announce this year. Maybe they're waiting until the second week of June (when E3 was going to happen), but I can't imagine we're going to get like 5 to 6 game reveals there. At this point we would need an E3 2017 level Direct to save Nintendo's 2020 lineup.

Wow, Arms in Smash? I honestly thought Nintendo and everyone else had forgotten about that game.
